Panau adusta is a moth in the family Cossidae. It was described by Roepke in 1957. It is found in Vietnam, Malaysia and on Sumatra, Java and Borneo. The habitat consists of alluvial forests, swamp forests, lowland dipterocarp forests and mangroves.
The forewings are bone grey with a blackish band from the basal third of the costa to the margin. The basal half of the forewing is divided by two black streaks enclosing a white or pale brown streak.